RESPONSIBLE DISCLOSURE:

Security vulnerabilities in identity and access management systems pose
significant risks. If you discover vulnerabilities:

1. Do not publicly disclose vulnerabilities before they are patched
2. Contact the project maintainers privately through designated channels
3. Provide detailed technical information about the vulnerability
4. Allow reasonable time for fixes before any public disclosure
5. Follow coordinated vulnerability disclosure practices
6. Consider the impact on users and organizations when timing disclosure

