DATA RETENTION AND DELETION:

Identity management systems process and store personal data that may be
subject to retention and deletion requirements:
- Implement appropriate data retention policies
- Provide mechanisms for data subject rights (access, rectification, erasure)
- Ensure secure deletion of personal data when required
- Maintain audit trails for data processing activities
- Regular review and cleanup of unused identity data

INCIDENT RESPONSE AND BREACH NOTIFICATION:

In the event of a security incident involving identity data:
- Implement comprehensive incident response procedures
- Notify affected individuals and authorities as required by law
- Document the incident and response actions taken
- Conduct post-incident analysis and improvement
- Update security controls based on lessons learned

TRAINING AND AWARENESS:

Organizations deploying this software should:
- Provide comprehensive training on identity security best practices
- Maintain awareness of emerging threats and vulnerabilities
- Regular security awareness training for all users
- Specialized training for privileged users and administrators
- Document and maintain security procedures and protocols

